2.title: A Duck in the Penthouse/Tour De Bugs
2.plot: Porky attempts to rid an annoying Daffy from a swanky penthouse apartment. Then, Bugs has a bike race against Cecil the Turtle. Bugs expects Cecil to be easily defeated, but the turtle has other plans.

3.plot: Sir Littlechin believes himself to the be the greatest swordsman in the land so Daffy decides to challenge him to a duel. Then, after Squeaks loses a bag of nuts playing pool with Shifty, Bugs decides it's time to teach Shifty a lesson.

4.title: Sam and the Bullet Train/Swine Dining
4.plot: Yosemite Sam believes no train is too fast to rob, until he goes head to head with a fancy new Bullet Train. Then, when Daffy discovers he's on the menu at Porky's restaurant, he decides to change the main ingredient to mayhem.

5.title: Love Is in the Hare/Valentine's Dayffy
5.plot: Bugs' day at the lake is interrupted by Yosemite Sam. To get Sam off his back, Bugs puts Sam through obstacles and a full makeover. Then, on Valentine's Day, Daffy runs into Cupid and knocks him out. Cupid tells Daffy to spread love.

6.title: Bigs Bunny/Wahder, Wahder, Everywhere
6.plot: A search for food lands Bugs and Squeaks in a run-in with the Barbarian and Krakos the Bear. Then, before his home lake is drained away, Daffy has to step in to stop Elmer Fudd's water bottling business.

7.title: Porky the Disorderly/Game, Set, Wabbit
7.plot: When Daffy runs wild in a hospital, it's up to Porky to get him to leave but Daffy has different plans. Then, Bugs serves up trouble as he teaches Viktor a lesson in humility competing for the championship at the tennis tournament.

11.title: Daffy the Stowaway/Superscooter 3000
11.plot: Daffy stows away on a cruise liner and Porky must make sure he's not discovered before he wreaks havoc on the ship. Then, Claudette is foiled by Bugs, who takes her scooter and secret documents on his tour of the Italian countryside.

12.title: Hoggin' the Road/Timmmmmmbugs
12.plot: Porky rents an RV for his cross-country road trip and picks up a wounded Daffy who takes Porky on a ride he never signed up for. Then, Bugs faces Blacque Jacque Shellacque in an old-fashioned lumberjack showdown, and the forest is at stake.

13.title: Easter Bunny Imposter/Easter Tweets
13.plot: A troupe of boy scouts mistake Bugs for the Easter Bunny and attempt to capture him by any means necessary. Then, it's Easter Sunday and Granny hires a sitter to watch Tweety. When the sitter winds up being Sylvester, it's cat versus bird.

14.title: Hoarder Up/Cougar, Cougar
14.plot: Unable to relax, Porky orders a hot tub from Daffy Duck. When Daffy shows up to install it, he takes Porky's home from cluttered mess to total pig sty. Then, while delivering pizzas, Bugs finds himself lured into the home of Miss Cougar.

15.title: The Wedding Quacksher/The Food Notwork
15.plot: Daffy crashes a wedding. Leslie P. Lillylegs must get rid of the duck. Then, Ivana hosts a cooking show and unknowingly involves Bugs when she steals his carrots. Bugs sabotages the live show proving revenge is a dish best served cold.

16.title: A Duck in the Aquarium/The BreezeHammer
16.plot: Daffy infiltrates the aquarium to get free food and it's up to aquarium worker Porky to get him out. Then, Bugs and Squeaks' day of kite flying is disrupted by Boyd the Bird, who falls madly in love with their kite.

17.title: Quantum Sheep/Houston, We Have a Duck Problem
17.plot: When Bugs and Squeaks discover Dr. Clovenhoof has built a time machine, the three go on a journey through time at different ages. Beware those awkward teenage years! Then, Astronaut Porky is assigned to place a transmitter on Mars.

18.title: 10-4 Good Bunny/Gold Medal Wabbit
18.plot: Bugs and Squeaks are hauling a piano in a cross-country road trip when they are sidetracked by corrupt sheriff Yosemite Sam. Then, Bugs unintentionally crashes the World Games and is forced to go up against an overconfident Calzone.

19.title: Cyrano de Bugs/Point Duck Percent
19.plot: When Leslie P. Lillylegs tries to woo Granny and steal her money, Bugs foils his plan by giving him terrible romantic advice. Then, Pampreen Perdy's mansion is up for a neighborhood beautification award but Daffy may ruin her chances.

20.title: Sir Littlechin and the Kraken/"Crouching Porky, Hidden Daffy
20.plot: Sir Littlechin hopes to capture the Kraken and mistakes Bugs for the beast. Bugs learns the actual Kraken is a kind soul and protects it. Then, Zen Master Elmer Fudd sends Porky to escort a sacred pickle to the temple of I-Ate-A-Tomoto.

21.title: King Nutininkommen/Greenhouse Gasbag
21.plot: Porky and Daffy stumble into the tomb of King Nutininkommen, and have to get out again before the mummy catches up with them. Then, an angry environmentalist picks the wrong person to stop for a donation when he flags down Foghorn Leghorn.

22.title: AbracaWabbit/Ponce de Calzone
22.plot: Bugs is upset when he stumbles upon Viktor demonstrating his tricks on a helpless bunny. Bugs agrees to be Viktor's assistant in exchange for letting the bunny go. Then, Explorer Ponce de Calzone is searching for the Fountain of Youth.

23.title: For the Love of Fraud/Not So Special Delivery
23.plot: When Squeaks spends his life savings on Foghorn's fraudulent snake oil, Bugs has no choice but to beat the bird at his own game. Then, Porky and Daffy are on duty delivering babies to expecting parents.

24.title: One Carroter in Search of an Artist/The Duck Days of Summer
24.plot: Bugs is in the middle of a cartoon adventure when he and the artist get into an argument. They both try and reboot the cartoon to mixed results. Then, Daffy can't handle his own celebrity when Elmer turns him into a symbol of summer.

25.title: Etiquette Shmetiquette/Daffy in the Science Museum
25.plot: Pepe visits a seaside bistro and lays his eyes on Claudette for the first time. It is love at first sight for the next five minutes or so. Then, Museum Guide Porky Pig hopes to get a group of scouts excited about the science museum.

26.title: Tad the Bachelor/Affaire du Jour
26.plot: Tad Tucker tries to find love on a dating show. When Bugs finds out he ate a family of rabbits, he seeks revenge. Then, Granny and Tweety run a charm school for chickens. When Daffy sees how well they're eating, he crashes his way in.

27.title: Top Bugs/Slugsmoby
27.plot: Ace fighter pilot Bugs Bunny is the best pilot at the Top Wing Fighter Pilot School until his nemesis Cecil starts breaking all of his records. Then, Captain Blacque Jacque Shellaque is searching the high seas for the mythical Slugsmoby.

28.title: Rhoda Rage/Good Duck to You Cirque
28.plot: Bugs attends a MMA match and sees champion fighter Rhoda Roundhouse cheating. When he calls her out, she challenges him to a fight and the match is on. Then, Viktor is a clown in the Pretentious Circus when his act is ruined by Daffy Duck.

29.title: Then Things Got Weird/Duck Duck Ghost
29.plot: When kids get lost in the mall, Bugs entertains them with a strange and imaginative tale until their mom comes. Then, Porky is determined to get his Halloween candy back from Daffy, who's hiding in a creepy looking house.

30.title: Acme Instant/When Marvin Comes Martian In
30.plot: When Wile E. Coyote discovers the secret behind AcmeInstant's instant delivery service is Road Runner, he pulls out all the stops to try and capture him. Then, Marvin the Martian plans an invasion of Earth but must study an Earthling first.

31.title: The Knight Time Is the Right Time/The Pepé Le Pew Affair
31.plot: Leslie is jealous when Bugs is appointed the new Knight of Square Table, so he tries everything to take Bugs out and replace him. Then, Pepe Le Pew and Claudette are assigned the same mission in an art gallery.

32.title: Hamsters/Bugs Baked
32.plot: Bugs agrees to take care of Porky's two hamsters. He brings them home, and wakes up the next morning to find out the hamsters have multiplied. Then, Bugs and Cecil each get half of the last dozen potato balls from a popular food truck.

1.plot: After pillaging a monastery, Yosemite Sam attempts to outwit an enlightened Bugs Bunny to receive the treasure of a lifetime. / When Squeaks finds himself up against a small group of ninjas, Bugs has to come to the rescue.

2.title: The Inside Bugs/Sun Valley Freeze
2.plot: Yosemite Sam hopes to make a quick escape from a bank heist, and is surprised to discover Bugs as his getaway driver. / Bugs must do everything he can to protect Bigfoot while not becoming collateral damage himself.

3.title: St. Bugs and the Dragon/Leaf It Alone
3.plot: Sir Littlechin the Knight is on a quest to capture a dragon, but not if Bugs has anything to do with it. / Wile E. Coyote attempts to show Bugs the future of yard maintenance, with limited results.

4.title: The Bigfoot in Bed/World Wide Wabbit

5.title: For the Love of Acorns/The Game Is a Foot
5.plot: Bugs and Squeks help a baby dragon escape a dragon slayer.

7.title: White House Wabbit/Bugsbarian
7.plot: Bugs takes a trip to Washington, D.C., where he is mistaken for the "First Rabbit." / A Barbarian and his trusty polar bear, Krakos, stake claim to the entire forest - including Bugs' home.

8.title: Not Lyin' Lion/Ice Ice Bunny
8.plot: Bugs and Squeaks head to the African Savanna to visit Squeaks' cousin, but first they have to outsmart the very hungry King of the Jungle, Thes. / Bugs is excited for a day of fun in the sun, so when the Winter Stag shows up, delivering Winter long before it's due, Bugs intervenes.

9.title: Wabbit's Wild/All Belts Are Off
9.plot: Squeaks hosts a last-minute card game at Bugs' house. Bugs is thrilled, until Shifty, a con artist, shows up to ruin the fun. / Yosemite Sam needs a belt, so he robs a men's clothing store. Bugs appears to save the day!

10.title: Wabbit's Best Friend/Annoying Ex-Boydfriend
10.plot: Bugs comes face to face with Jack the Dog Trainer. It's up to him to rescue a pack of dogs. A boy bird named Boyd tries to win back his girlfriend through midnight serenades. Bugs, who is desperate for sleep, realizes the only way to get Boyd to stop is to help.

11.title: Bugs Vs Snail/To Catch a Fairy
11.plot: Bugs is looking forward to a day of kite flying. First, however, he must make it out his front door and he's stuck inside with a gratuity-wanting delivery snail. / When Bugs wakes up to discover his teeth missing, he must go head to head with an ornery tooth fairy to get them back.

12.title: Bugs in the Garden/Scarecrow
12.plot: Bugs and Wile E. Coyote compete in a garden grow-off! It's nature versus science! May the best man win. / Bugs' trusty GPS gets him lost in a cornfield, where a very scatterbrained Scarecrow desperately tries to do his job.

13.title: Painter Paint Hare/The Spy Who Bugged Me
13.plot: Jack decides to take up nature painting, only to bring chaos to the forest. Bugs confronts him and mayhem ensues.

14.title: Hareplane Mode/Bugs of Steel
14.plot: After a run-in with Bugs, Yosemite Sam's cell phone gets scratched. He decides it's time to upgrade, but little does he know that Bugs is there to help. / Rock Hardcase, a fitness guru, shows up to pull a fast one on the unsuspecting animals of the forest. Bugs proves to be an extremely difficult customer. A Boomerang original.

15.title: Big Troubles/Manner Maid
15.plot: When Squeaks takes Bugs to visit his cousin, they cross paths with an idiotic lion.

16.title: Carrot Before the Horse/Trunk with Power
16.plot: An entitled little girl named Pampreen takes all of Bugs' carrots for her prize pony Puddin. Bugs and Squeaks go on a mission to get them back. / Bugs is running late to catch his flight, but first must get past a toll tree in dire need of an attitude adjustment.

17.title: Bugsfoot/Grim on Vacation
17.plot: Bugs attempts the path less traveled, and finds himself in yet another stand-off between the Hazmats and Bigfoot. / The Grim Rabbit takes a vacation, only to discover Bugs is there too. Despite his wife's ultimatum of "No Smiting," the Grim Rabbit is set on trying to mix business with pleasure.

18.title: Snow Wabbit/Aromatherapest
18.plot: Bugs and a Snowman fight over who should get the carrot. / Bugs and Wile get skunked. Who has the better way to recover from such a smelly situation? It's nature versus science! May the best man win!

19.title: Raising Your Spirits/Dust Bugster
19.plot: A Ghost visits Bugs and battles him for his bedsheet. / Bugs allows his house to get so dirty a giant dust bunny forms. When Bugs decides the house isn't big enough for the two of them, a battle ensues.

20.title: Computer Bugs/Oils Well That Ends Well
20.plot: A computer virus invades Bugs' computer. Bugs goes inside the mainframe to fight him. / Bugs mistakes the makeshift oil field of thieving oil tycoon Ivana for the Burning Man Festival. As she tries to make off with the oil, Bugs spoils all her fun.

21.title: Your Bunny or Your Life/Misjudgement Day
21.plot: Grim is after Bugs again and a chase ensues. / A terminator robot is sent to destroy Bugs. None of Bugs' usual gags work.
